<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870807-0032 </DOCNO><HL> Grey Advertising Inc.</HL><DD> 08/07/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GREYDIVIDENDS (DIV) </IN><TEXT>   GREY ADVERTISING INC. said its directors approved a 10% increase in the quarterly dividend, to 55 cents a share from 50 cents, payable Sept. 15 to stock of record Sept. 1. The New York-based advertising and public relations concern also reported that its second-quarter earnings rose 12%, to $4.1 million, or $2.92 a share. Gross billings for the period increased 17%, to $537.8 million. The company said the dividend increase reflects a &quot;somewhat more favorable trend developing&quot; in the business. </TEXT></DOC>